## üìù Tips for Parents and Teachers

**How to Use This Workbook:**
1. Have your child read one story at a time
2. Let them answer questions independently first
3. Review answers together and discuss critical thinking questions
4. Celebrate effort and improvement!

**Reading Strategies to Practice:**
- üìå Point to words while reading
- üîä Read aloud together
- ‚ùì Ask "what do you think will happen?" before finishing
- üé® Draw a picture of the story after reading

**Signs of Progress:**
- Answering questions without looking back at the text
- Making connections between stories and real life
- Asking their own questions about what they read
- Showing interest in reading more!

